<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="antibiotic_resistance_gene">Antibiotic Resistance Gene</a> - These <a href="#gene">genes</a> create a product that confers antibiotic resistance. For example, KanR confers resistance to the antibiotic kanamycin. This is often used for <a href="#selection">selection</a> of microorganisms or others.